      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As the name suggests, everything in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Voice Of Cards: The Isle Dragon Roars ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "is portrayed entirely as cards. Characters are cards, enemies are cards, items are cards, even the world itself is made of cards. Alongside this, the random battles are done on a separate table with dice sets and counters, leading to this game having a very unique art style.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The battle system is a typical turn-based affair but with a slight difference. Whenever your party members take an action in combat, it generates a gem. These gems can be spent on stronger abilities or spells in combat which helps to spice up the combat system.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Every character, including the monsters, have their own backstory. After fulfilling some prerequisite requirements, you can unlock a certain character’s, NPC’s or monster’s backstory which helps to flesh out the world and make it feel lived in. One minute you’ll be helping out an old woman who has sprained her ankle to get to an apothecary and in the next, you’ll unlock her backstory and learn that her husband is missing and she’s been eating a lot of meat-heavy meals lately.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
