      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Bad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When going into a game like this, especially one with Yoko Taro’s name plastered all over it, you’re going to expect a fantastic story with a possible deconstruction of the genre he’s working with; sadly, you will not get that here. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Voice Of Cards: The Isle Dragon Roars",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has probably the most boring and cliché plot I’ve ever experienced in an RPG! Imagine a group of tabletop RPG players getting ready for their game to start, only for their Game Master to cancel at the last second so one of the players makes up a story on the spot and runs the game to not disappoint the rest of the group - that's how this game’s story feels like it was written.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Voice Of Cards: The Isle Dragon Roars",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " only has one voice actor - the narrator (or Game Master, in this case) - who is voiced by Todd Haberkorn. I know Todd Haberkorn is a great voice actor, he’s voiced some of my favourite characters like ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Soul Eater’s",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " Death The Kid and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Persona 4 Arena: Ultimax",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "’s Sho Minazuki but his performance here is really bland; he sounds like he’s bored and doesn’t want to be there. In situations like this, this is more a fault with the voice director rather than the actor themselves as we know he’s a talented individual.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With the whole game being presented through cards, you wouldn’t think there’d be any loading issues in a game like this. When I say everything is made out of cards, I mean ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "everything",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". Each UI element is it’s own separate card, which means when you’re cycling through menus, the game has to constantly load and unload each card which leads to a lot of slow down. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
